choices.text: international community. I'm completely isolated from more than 10 years age group (25-30 or older) because I've left Estonia many, many years ago and didn't get back since. In my personal life, the only friends that I have from this age group are married couples, often with their young children. Apart from that, there are a few friends that are around 15 years younger than I am. The topic of discussion and general attitude is very different. After returning to Estonia in 2016, I found myself struggling even more with this issue, because Estonia today simply doesn't appeal to me at all. Not once did I have a chance to visit some interesting place in Estonia or explore some new activity worth spending my time. In Estonia today you have to have your own money to be able to explore all these foreign or national small ways of gaming the system. Friends from my age bracket that I'm in contact with nowadays, I've visited with a lot of ease via cheap flights and they have perfectly no idea whatsoever how to escape Estonia. That's directly caused by the fact that today Estonia is aimed towards consumer attitude and not towards the pioneers that made it possible to be what it is today. In practical terms, you need to work very hard to live well in Estonia and I have no intention of doing so.
